					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>411 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>330</height>
										<width>230</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>411 folios (+2 unfoliated flyleaves at the beginning and at the ned of the manuscript). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally 41 quires of 10 leaves.  </p>
									<p>A number of lacunas in the first 4 and the last 10 quires. The first quire is defective. </p>
									<p>Folios 1-37 contain 4 quires signed with Hebrew letters on the first page; folios 38-307 have 27 quires signed with Hebrew letters on first page; folios 308-410 contain more than 10 quires signed with Hebrew letters on the first and the last page. </p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="17" writtenLines="17">
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning and at the end. </p>
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Yemenite square and semi-cursive script, punctuated, of the 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Mosheh ben ῾Amram ibn Naṣr ben ῾Ezra ibn Ḥābish</name>; inscribed with his name in the colophon, 305r and on folios 54r, 240r:אנא ספרא משה בן עמרם בן עזרא, (כתבתי זאת התורה ואני בן שבע ושלושים שנה).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<decoDesc>
							<summary>Two full-page illuminated borders. Masorah in micrographic designs.</summary>
